Chapter 1. Admin Guide

1.1. Overview

   The rust_concurrent_calls module provides per-account concurrent
   call limiting for OpenSIPS. It tracks active calls per account
   (typically identified by From-URI username) and enforces
   configurable per-account limits loaded from a CSV file.

   Accounts not listed in the limits file are subject to a
   configurable default limit. An account with a limit of 0 is
   effectively blocked from making any calls.

1.2. How it works

   The module uses explicit increment/decrement calls from the
   OpenSIPS script rather than dialog callbacks. This design keeps
   the module simple and gives the script author full control over
   when counts are adjusted.

   Typical usage:
     1. On initial INVITE (no to-tag): call rust_check_concurrent()
        to verify the account is under its limit. If allowed, call
        rust_concurrent_inc() to increment the counter.
     2. On failure responses (3xx-6xx to INVITE): call
        rust_concurrent_dec() to release the slot.
     3. On BYE: call rust_concurrent_dec() to release the slot.

   Per-account limits are loaded from a CSV file at worker startup.
   Each worker maintains its own independent set of counters, so
   the effective limit is per-worker. For precise global limiting,
   consider using an external data store.

   The rust_check_concurrent() function sets $var(concurrent_count)
   and $var(concurrent_limit) pseudo-variables for use in script
   logging or response messages.

1.3. Dependencies

1.3.1. OpenSIPS Modules

   The following modules must be loaded before this module:
     * None.

1.3.2. External Libraries or Applications

   The following libraries or applications must be installed
   before running OpenSIPS with this module loaded:
     * None.

1.4. Exported Parameters

1.4.1. limits_file (string)

   Path to a CSV file defining per-account concurrent call limits.
   Format: one line per account as "account,max_calls". Lines
   starting with # are treated as comments. Blank lines are
   ignored. This parameter is required.

   Default value is "None" (must be set).

   Example 1.1. Set limits_file parameter
...
modparam("rust_concurrent_calls", "limits_file", "/etc/opensips/call_limits.csv")
...

   Example 1.3. Limits file format
# /etc/opensips/call_limits.csv
# account,max_calls
alice,5
bob,20
sip_trunk_1,100
blocked_user,0

1.4.2. default_limit (integer)

   Default concurrent call limit applied to accounts not listed in
   the limits file.

   Default value is "10".

   Example 1.2. Set default_limit parameter
...
modparam("rust_concurrent_calls", "default_limit", 5)
...

1.5. Exported Functions

1.5.1. rust_check_concurrent(account)

   Check whether the given account is under its concurrent call
   limit. On return, the pseudo-variables $var(concurrent_count)
   and $var(concurrent_limit) are set to the current count and
   the effective limit for the account.

   This function does NOT increment the counter. Use
   rust_concurrent_inc() separately after a successful check.

   Parameters:
     * account (string) - The account identifier to check.
       Typically $fU (From-URI username) or $rU (Request-URI
       username). This parameter is mandatory.

   Return values:
     * 1 - account is under its limit (allowed)
     * -1 - account is at or over its limit (blocked)

   This function can be used from REQUEST_ROUTE, FAILURE_ROUTE,
   and ONREPLY_ROUTE.

   Example 1.4. rust_check_concurrent usage
...
route {
    if (is_method("INVITE") && !has_totag()) {
        if (!rust_check_concurrent("$fU")) {
            xlog("L_WARN", "$fU over limit: $var(concurrent_count)/$var(concurrent_limit)\n");
            sl_send_reply(486, "Too Many Calls");
            exit;
        }
    }
}
...

1.5.2. rust_concurrent_inc(account)

   Increment the concurrent call counter for the given account.
   Call this after a successful rust_check_concurrent() when the
   INVITE is being forwarded.

   Parameters:
     * account (string) - The account identifier. Must match the
       value used in rust_check_concurrent(). This parameter is
       mandatory.

   Return values:
     * 1 - counter incremented successfully
     * -1 - error (missing parameter or uninitialized worker)

   This function can be used from REQUEST_ROUTE, FAILURE_ROUTE,
   and ONREPLY_ROUTE.

   Example 1.5. rust_concurrent_inc usage
...
route {
    if (is_method("INVITE") && !has_totag()) {
        if (rust_check_concurrent("$fU")) {
            rust_concurrent_inc("$fU");
        }
    }
}
...

1.5.3. rust_concurrent_dec(account)

   Decrement the concurrent call counter for the given account.
   The counter floors at zero and will never go negative.

   Call this when a call ends (BYE) or when an INVITE receives a
   failure response and the counter was previously incremented.

   Parameters:
     * account (string) - The account identifier. Must match the
       value used in rust_concurrent_inc(). This parameter is
       mandatory.

   Return values:
     * 1 - counter decremented successfully
     * -1 - error (missing parameter or uninitialized worker)

   This function can be used from REQUEST_ROUTE, FAILURE_ROUTE,
   and ONREPLY_ROUTE.

   Example 1.6. rust_concurrent_dec usage
...
route[handle_bye] {
    rust_concurrent_dec("$fU");
}
...

1.6. Exported Pseudo-Variables

   The following pseudo-variables are set by
   rust_check_concurrent():

1.6.1. $var(concurrent_count)

   The current number of active calls for the checked account.
   Set as an integer by rust_check_concurrent().

1.6.2. $var(concurrent_limit)

   The effective concurrent call limit for the checked account.
   Set as an integer by rust_check_concurrent(). This is either
   the per-account limit from the limits file or the default_limit
   if the account is not listed.

1.7. Exported Statistics

1.7.1. checked

   Total number of concurrent call checks performed.

1.7.2. allowed

   Number of checks where the account was under its limit.

1.7.3. blocked

   Number of checks where the account was at or over its limit.

1.7.4. incremented

   Total number of counter increments (rust_concurrent_inc calls).

1.7.5. decremented

   Total number of counter decrements (rust_concurrent_dec calls).

1.7.6. accounts

   Number of accounts loaded from the limits file at startup.

   Example 1.7. Complete opensips.cfg example
...
loadmodule "rust_concurrent_calls.so"

modparam("rust_concurrent_calls", "limits_file", "/etc/opensips/call_limits.csv")
modparam("rust_concurrent_calls", "default_limit", 10)

route {
    if (is_method("INVITE") && !has_totag()) {
        # Check concurrent call limit
        if (!rust_check_concurrent("$fU")) {
            xlog("L_WARN", "BLOCKED: $fU at $var(concurrent_count)/$var(concurrent_limit) calls\n");
            sl_send_reply(486, "Too Many Calls");
            exit;
        }
        # Under limit — increment counter and forward
        rust_concurrent_inc("$fU");
    }

    if (is_method("BYE")) {
        rust_concurrent_dec("$fU");
    }
}

onreply_route {
    # Decrement on failure responses to initial INVITE
    if (is_method("INVITE") && $rs >= 300) {
        rust_concurrent_dec("$fU");
    }
}
...
